{{nihongo|'''Keisuke Ōsako'''|大迫 敬介|Ōsako Keisuke|born 28 July 1999}} is a Japanese [[association football|footballer]] who currently plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{Japanese football updater|SanfrecH}} club [[Sanfrecce Hiroshima]] and the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]].

==International career==
On May 24, 2019, Ōsako was called up by [[Japan national football team|Japan]]'s head coach [[Hajime Moriyasu]] to feature in the [[2019 Copa América|Copa América]] played in Brazil.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jfa.jp/eng/news/00021323/|title=SAMURAI BLUE (Japan National Team) Squad, Schedule - CONMEBOL Copa America Brazil 2019 (6/14–7/7)|publisher=JFA|date=24 May 2019}}</ref> He debuted on June 17, 2019, in the opening Copa game against Chile, as a starter.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[CONMEBOL]]|url=http://estadisticas.conmebol.com/html/v3/index.html?channel=deportes.futbol.copaamerica.462516&lang=es_LA|title=Japan v Chile game report|date=17 June 2019}}</ref>

On 15 May 2026, Ōsako was named in Japan's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |title=SAMURAI BLUE（日本代表）メンバー・スケジュール キリンチャレンジカップ2026 ひとつになるから強くなる。 5.31 アイスランド代表戦（5.31 東京／国立競技場）FIFAワールドカップ2026（6.11-7.19 カナダ・メキシコ・アメリカ） |url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/news/00036338/ |website=www.jfa.jp |access-date=15 May 2026 |language=ja}}</ref>

